1
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,133
<i>I'm just here to collect the
rest of what you owe.</i>

2
00:00:02,267 --> 00:00:03,267
<i> Do you own this hotel now?</i>

3
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:04,600
<i> Didn't I tell you to wait?</i>

4
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:05,933
<i> I'll pay you, Bok.</i>

5
00:00:06,067 --> 00:00:07,967
- [SCREAMS]
- Jade!

6
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:09,467
<i>- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?</i>

7
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:12,333
<i> Sir, I have good news for you.</i>

8
00:00:12,467 --> 00:00:14,233
<i>There's a new candidate
you'll be interviewing</i>

9
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:16,167
<i> to be your assistant.</i>

10
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,133
<i>It's fine.
I don't need a new assistant.</i>

11
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,800
<i> About the flowers,</i>

12
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:21,067
<i> who sent them?</i>

13
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,533
<i>What kind of flowers
were these again, Ma?</i>

14
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:24,433
<i>The same ones your dad
used to give.</i>

15
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:25,500
<i> Waling-waling.</i>

16
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:28,733
<i>Didn't the police return
your father's phone?</i>

17
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:30,467
<i>Maybe we can find
something there.</i>

18
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,533
[DOOR OPENS]

19
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:37,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,933
[DOOR CLOSES]

21
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:40,367
[SIGHS]

22
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:59,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:21,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

24
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:31,700
[MUSIC GROWS TENSE]

25
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:38,433
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

26
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:45,133
[DOOR SLAMS]

27
00:01:46,767 --> 00:01:53,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

28
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:03,667
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

29
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:04,800
[DOOR OPENS]

30
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:13,800
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

31
00:03:06,267 --> 00:03:13,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,367
There!

33
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:32,167
Finally, I found it.

34
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:39,933
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [OBJECT CLATTERING]

35
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:48,267
[DOOR OPENS]

36
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:53,633
Uh...

37
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,767
Martin.

38
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,233
You're still awake?

39
00:03:56,967 --> 00:03:58,200
[MARTIN] I can't sleep.

40
00:03:58,333 --> 00:03:59,600
What about you?

41
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:01,800
Same here.

42
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:03,433
Ah, do you want some...

43
00:04:03,567 --> 00:04:04,333
milk?

44
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:05,767
Monette has milk there.

45
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,900
Wasn't that what Papa used
to give us to help us sleep?

46
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:10,400
Let's go.

47
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:16,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:17,767
Oh.

49
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,367
Gio.

50
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,833
You can't sleep either?

51
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,433
Do you have a minute?

52
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:29,800
I just wanted to tell you
something.

53
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:31,367
[MILK POURING]

54
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,000
That guy's crazy, huh!

55
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:34,667
He beat you up?

56
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:36,767
Was that the one from room 203?

57
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,667
- I'll take care of it.
- [GLASS THUDS]

58
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,600
[CHAIR SLIDES]

59
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,000
I just really wanted
to let you know.

60
00:04:44,767 --> 00:04:45,733
I feel like...

61
00:04:45,867 --> 00:04:48,933
he just wanted to make sure
I would really pay.

62
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,600
W-Wait.

63
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:54,267
You mean that's the Bok
you owe money to?

64
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,867
He followed you here?

65
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:58,133
Looks like he's still
not satisfied

66
00:04:58,267 --> 00:04:59,467
with what I already paid.

67
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,433
[SIGHS]

68
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,967
W-Wait-- How did he know
you were here?

69
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,900
Martin, social media.

70
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:06,833
It's really easy, especially...

71
00:05:06,967 --> 00:05:08,600
people recognize us
because of Edward,

72
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:10,933
and because of those
influencer friends of his.

73
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:16,300
Sorry about that.

74
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:17,633
[SIGHS]

75
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:19,967
I tried to drive him away,
but...

76
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,167
that bastard really
has some nerve.

77
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:25,633
It's a bit concerning,
but it's good that you told us.

78
00:05:25,767 --> 00:05:27,533
At least we know
what to expect, right?

79
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:31,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:33,567
If I could just drag him
out of here,

81
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:36,200
- I would've done it already.
- [CHUCKLING]

82
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:37,533
[MARTIN] Hey...

83
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:40,067
We'll have security
keep an eye on him, okay?

84
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,367
Thank you, Martin.

85
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:43,433
But Gio, if you ever
need backup,

86
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:44,900
I'm right here.

87
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:47,933
I may not have abs,
but I'm a strongman.

88
00:05:48,067 --> 00:05:49,267
- [SCOFFS]
- [CHUCKLES]

89
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,533
Whatever you say.

90
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,433
Abs? Abs.

91
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:53,867
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,367
[VAN ENGINE RUNNING]

93
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:03,067
[ROI YAWNS]

94
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:11,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:06:12,967 --> 00:06:14,567
Roi, are you sleepy?

96
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,667
Ma'am?

97
00:06:16,733 --> 00:06:18,467
I'm asking if you're sleepy.

98
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,900
Because if yes, I'll drive.

99
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:23,533
It's dangerous if
you're driving while sleepy.

100
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,300
Uh... [CHUCKLES]

101
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:28,500
No, ma'am. I'm fine.

102
00:06:28,633 --> 00:06:31,633
Uh... I just didn't
sleep well last night,

103
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,167
but...

104
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,667
I can manage.

105
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:40,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

106
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,067
What?

107
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:48,267
Suppliers, stage setup,
lights, sounds, permit,

108
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,400
- security--
- Sir!

109
00:06:49,533 --> 00:06:50,467
Have you checked
the generator?

110
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,733
- Sir, breathe. Inhale, exhale.
- Sari!

111
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:55,233
It's all set, sir!
Look, check, check!

112
00:06:55,367 --> 00:06:57,000
The artist contract,
did you get it signed?

113
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:58,133
- [SARI] Oh!
- Where is it?

114
00:06:58,267 --> 00:07:00,333
Yes, Sir. It's here.
Wait a second.

115
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:01,500
[MARTIN] Let me see!

116
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:03,000
Wait, sir. It's right here.

117
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,700
Sari! Artist contract?!

118
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,200
Sari, the contract!

119
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:08,933
Sari, where's the contract?!

120
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:11,900
[SARI] Sir! I caught it!

121
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:13,333
Sir, here it is!

122
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:14,700
Here's the contract!

123
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,400
I did it, sir!

124
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:18,067
[SARI SQUEALS]

125
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:20,267
[SIGHS] Raphie!

126
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,000
Sir! Sir...

127
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:23,700
Sir!

128
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,133
[CHUCKLES]

129
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:27,967
[MAN GRUNTING]

130
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,067
[JADE] Let's go here.
Quick.

131
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,200
- Come on, come on.
- Jade...

132
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:34,000
my brothers might look
for me.

133
00:07:34,133 --> 00:07:36,067
They won't. We'll be quick.

134
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,233
Promise.

135
00:07:37,367 --> 00:07:44,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

136
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:48,533
- [JADE] Kiko, Kiko.
- [KIKO] Oh?

137
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:51,533
You know, I have a
strong feeling about this.

138
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:53,600
I feel like this is also
where we'll find

139
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:55,900
the answers to our questions.

140
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:57,467
You know what? Me too.

141
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,200
I almost got caught last night.

142
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,767
OMG.

143
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:01,867
Twins.

144
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,700
Twins?

145
00:08:04,267 --> 00:08:05,333
Us? [CHUCKLES]

146
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:07,400
What is that, like gecko twins
or something?

147
00:08:07,533 --> 00:08:09,533
No! I mean, me too.

148
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:11,233
I almost got caught
last night too.

149
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:13,833
Oh! Twins!

150
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:17,267
Whatever, Kiko!
Let's just go.

151
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,033
Here, this way.

152
00:08:19,167 --> 00:08:20,200
Let's go here.

153
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,300
Here, here.
There's a path here.

154
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:25,200
Let's pass here. There.

155
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:27,667
Just stay quiet, okay? Slowly.

156
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:31,933
Kiko, is there a path there?

157
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:33,667
- Let's check.
- Let's check. Come on.

158
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:38,467
There's no path here anymore.

159
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,900
Where are we?

160
00:08:40,033 --> 00:08:41,467
Here, here.
Let's just stay here.

161
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,933
- Okay.
- Come on.

162
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:45,467
- Game.
- [THUDS]

163
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,267
- [CRACKS]
- [SCREAMS]

164
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:51,067
- Are you okay?
- Ow! Kiko!

165
00:08:51,067 --> 00:08:53,133
You said we'd go slow?!

166
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:54,933
Oh my god! It's always like this

167
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:55,933
- when we're together,
- Ow, ow! My phone!

168
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,633
- something unlucky happens!
- My phone!

169
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,100
Excuse me?

170
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:03,267
Are you saying
I'm the unlucky one?

171
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:04,967
I didn't say that.

172
00:09:04,967 --> 00:09:06,667
You just implied it, right?

173
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:09,733
What I'm saying is,
something unlucky happened,

174
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:11,967
I didn't say it's you.

175
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:13,567
You're always so paranoid.

176
00:09:13,567 --> 00:09:14,533
Okay.

177
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,400
Okay, you have a point, that...

178
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,433
or maybe the universe
is trying to tell us something.

179
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:21,733
Like what? That we
shouldn't be doing this?

180
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:24,333
That we shouldn't
doubt your mom?

181
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:28,333
Kiko, I'll say it again.
I just want the truth.

182
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:32,067
And this time, hopefully, the
universe is on our side, right?

183
00:09:32,067 --> 00:09:35,767
[KIKO] Universe, please, grant
us this one thing, please.

184
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:38,333
Where's the phone? Where is it?

185
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,333
Oh... never mind.
Here it is.

186
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,300
- Game?
- What? So? Should we open it?

187
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:46,633
Game. Three, two, one.

188
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:53,500
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

189
00:09:58,033 --> 00:10:02,000
One, two, three, go!

190
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:06,267
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

191
00:10:06,267 --> 00:10:07,567
Yes! Oh my god!

192
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:09,767
- Yes! Ah!
- [LAUGHS]

193
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:12,400
Uh... wow...
Thank you, universe!

194
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,500
What? What? Thank you...

195
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:17,300
Thank you! Thank you, universe!

196
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,300
[SQUEALS] Yay!

197
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,600
[SIGH OF HAPPINESS]

198
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,600
[EDWARD] Bro, thank you.

199
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,333
Thank you for coming.

200
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:29,133
You think I'd ever say no, bro?

201
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:30,567
That's what I'm talking about.

202
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:31,667
But how are you guys?

203
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,500
I'm excited
for your event.

204
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,500
Bro, this is gonna be huge.
Believe me.

205
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:37,133
- Yeah, I got this.
- Hope you brought more guests.

206
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:38,333
I got this, bro.

207
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:39,567
More of our friends
are coming tomorrow.

208
00:10:39,567 --> 00:10:41,333
- Really? Seriously?
- Yeah, seriously.

209
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,233
Nice one, nice one, nice one.
Let's go?

210
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:44,667
- Let's check your room.
- Let's go, let's go, let's go.

211
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:46,633
- Welcome to Hotel 88, sirs!
- Hello! Hello!

212
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:47,767
- Hi.
- For check-in?

213
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:49,333
This way.

214
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:51,400
Ma'am, get them room, please?

215
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,400
The bigger ones.
they are my friends.

216
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:56,367
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

217
00:10:56,367 --> 00:10:57,467
[CLEARS THROAT]

218
00:10:57,467 --> 00:10:59,433
- You're welcome.
- [MONETTE] You're in room 307.

219
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:02,700
Wow... no "thank you,"
straight to "you're welcome"?

220
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:05,200
I already guessed
what you'd say.

221
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:10,533
I knew I made the right call
getting you.

222
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:13,100
I know, right?

223
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,633
So? Let's go.

224
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,633
- All set?
- Yeah, all set.

225
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:17,833
- Let's go, let's go.
- Let's go. Thanks!

226
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,067
- Thank you, sir!
- Thank you.

227
00:11:19,067 --> 00:11:21,233
- Enjoy! Thank you.
- Thank you, thank you.

228
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:23,567
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,233
[RAPHIE]
Welcome, sir!

230
00:11:25,233 --> 00:11:26,567
[RECEPTIONIST]
Good morning, sir.

231
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:33,200
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:36,733
Uh...
Hello, welcome to Hotel 88.

233
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,167
For check-in?

234
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,367
Good morning, sir.
For check-in?

235
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,800
Can I get your ID?

236
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:50,633
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,333
Sir Martin is here.

238
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:57,533
He's just talking
to the lighting crew.

239
00:11:57,533 --> 00:12:00,600
There's a small problem,
you know?

240
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,867
But he's here.

241
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:05,233
We need to talk to them.

242
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,567
Oh, Sir Gio is here too.

243
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:09,667
But...

244
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:11,300
why are people wandering around?

245
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,733
Wait, I'll come back to you.

246
00:12:12,733 --> 00:12:14,733
I just need to find him.
Hold on.

247
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:21,333
[TRIXIE] Are the voltages
and wires all good?

248
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:23,767
We can't afford
a glitch later, okay?

249
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:25,467
Okay. Alright, thank you.

250
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:26,867
I'll introduce you
to the band's vocalist.

251
00:12:26,867 --> 00:12:28,100
He's my friend. We're close.

252
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,500
[CLICKS TONGUE]
I'm not interested, Justin.

253
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:31,567
- Then... shots?
- I don't drink.

254
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:34,867
B-But... Come on.
I'm just welcoming you.

255
00:12:34,867 --> 00:12:37,467
Why? Because you found out
I'm Martin's sister?

256
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:40,467
No, I just want to give you
a proper welcome.

257
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,900
[SIGHS SHARPLY] If you're
the one doing it, I'd pass.

258
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:45,167
Oh man.
No... wait, wait, wait.

259
00:12:45,167 --> 00:12:47,733
Can you stop doing that?

260
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,633
No.

261
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:52,567
The more you walk away,
the more

262
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,833
you'll see this face.

263
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,400
Oh god.

264
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,600
[CHUCKLES]

265
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,300
- Miss Trixie, Sir Justin.
- Yes?

266
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:01,700
- Have you seen Sir Martin?
- No, why?

267
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,633
The police are looking for him.

268
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:04,600
Police?

269
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:07,933
Yeah. Okay,
I'll find him and come back.

270
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:10,500
Done? Ma'am?

271
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,300
- Ma'am. Can you check--
- Huh?

272
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,267
Jean, we're over budget.

273
00:13:14,267 --> 00:13:17,467
Their stage rig costs
way more than allocated.

274
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:19,667
That's what they gave me, sir.

275
00:13:19,667 --> 00:13:21,467
Try talking to them.

276
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,500
Production expenses
are exploding.

277
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:25,000
I'll try, Sir Leon.

278
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,267
Thank you.

279
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:31,600
[PHONE RINGING]

280
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,667
Justin.

281
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:38,633
[PHONE CHIMES]

282
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,633
[PHONE CHIMES]

283
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:43,900
Hello.

284
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,933
Wait, I'll find them. Sorry.

285
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:53,400
Jade hasn't answered yet.
Where is she?

286
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,933
[LUNA]<i> Justin, I'm busy
</i> at the hotel. What now?

287
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:59,267
The stupid police are here.

288
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:01,867
What are they doing here?

289
00:14:03,867 --> 00:14:06,400
[JUSTIN]
I don't know either.

290
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,667
But Sari's with them.

291
00:14:08,667 --> 00:14:10,633
They're looking for Martin.

292
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:13,400
What do they want
with Martin now?

293
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,000
Will those cops ever stop?

294
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,667
For now, we don't know why.

295
00:14:18,667 --> 00:14:21,300
They literally have
nothing better to do.

296
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:22,467
That's it.

297
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:27,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

298
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,333
[JADE]
Look at this.

299
00:14:29,367 --> 00:14:30,400
[PHONE BUZZING]

300
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,733
- "I miss you."
- "I miss you."

301
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:32,533
[JADE CHUCKLING]

302
00:14:32,533 --> 00:14:33,700
[KIKO]
You look really amused.

303
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:35,667
Those two are crazy
with their bromance.

304
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:38,800
But then again, they've always
been like that, even before.

305
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:41,700
[KIKO] Exactly. You know,
this is what really confuses me.

306
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:43,800
If they're that close,

307
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,900
would Papa really be able
to have a relationship

308
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:47,900
with your mom?

309
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:48,967
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

310
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:50,700
I don't know, Kiko.

311
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:54,300
I just have
this strange feeling.

312
00:14:57,433 --> 00:14:58,767
But look at this.

313
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:00,933
Look.

314
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,633
Their calls are back to back.

315
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,400
What do you think
they're talking about?

316
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:14,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:15:15,967 --> 00:15:17,733
[JUSTIN]
Luna said she's on her way.

318
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:20,467
Have they been here long?

319
00:15:21,467 --> 00:15:23,767
[SHARPLY EXHALES]
Feels like they just got here.

320
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,400
You know, I really don't like
the look on his face.

321
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,767
Makes me want to punch him.

322
00:15:30,067 --> 00:15:32,400
What do you think
they're talking about?

323
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:34,633
I thought the earring issue
was already settled.

324
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:35,967
So why are they here now?

325
00:15:35,967 --> 00:15:37,233
Do you want me to go over
and approach them, Leon?

326
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:39,000
I'll deal with them directly
so we can get this over with.

327
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Don't.

328
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:42,067
Don't?

329
00:15:42,067 --> 00:15:43,433
What, we just stay here?
Just stare at them?

330
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:44,767
Just stare at them?

331
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:48,667
[SCOFFS]

332
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:49,967
Thank you for coming.

333
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:51,600
This means a lot, sir.

334
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,667
Thanks.

335
00:15:56,767 --> 00:16:00,600
It's our job, after all
to make sure everyone is safe.

336
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,400
We'll be sending a few
more of our men.

337
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,633
They'll keep watch here
until tomorrow.

338
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:08,533
Will you be sending some
to Hotel 88 as well?

339
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,500
We also have guests
checked in there.

340
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:15,867
We'll check.

341
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:17,567
But the event is here.

342
00:16:17,567 --> 00:16:18,900
So the security
should be here too.

343
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:25,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:31,033
That makes sense...

345
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:34,100
Alright then, we'll handle
the security at Hotel 88.

346
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:37,000
But whatever happens,
you can still call us.

347
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:41,633
- We'll go now.
- Alright. Thank you again.

348
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,967
There, they left.

349
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:45,733
The Almazan brothers have been
staring at us for a while now.

350
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:46,933
Why do you think that is?

351
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:48,900
They're probably
just getting paranoid.

352
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:51,500
Good. I'm not letting them
off the hook.

353
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:58,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

354
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:05,133
Oh, looks like Martin's gone.

355
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:07,033
Oh, Luna!

356
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:09,733
What happened?

357
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:11,767
Did those police officers
talk to you?

358
00:17:11,767 --> 00:17:13,633
What did Martin say?

359
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:14,767
Did they approach you?

360
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:18,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:20,000
So, nothing happened?

362
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,533
Leon!

363
00:17:22,433 --> 00:17:24,067
I was waiting for them
to call me over or something,

364
00:17:24,067 --> 00:17:25,933
but... nothing.

365
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:28,067
They just talked
and then left right away.

366
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:29,667
What about Martin?
You didn't ask him?

367
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:34,667
They came up to us,
but they didn't say anything.

368
00:17:34,667 --> 00:17:36,000
I thought they might get
the wrong idea

369
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,800
if I started asking questions.

370
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,467
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

371
00:17:39,467 --> 00:17:41,633
Do you think this is still
about the earring?

372
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:43,200
I don't know.

373
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,667
I really don't know.

374
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:49,567
All I know is the four of us
have to stay united.

375
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,533
We can't fall apart.

376
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:52,800
Four?

377
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,867
But there are only three of us
right now.

378
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:56,467
Where's Jade?

379
00:17:56,467 --> 00:17:57,733
Nothing.
She still hasn't replied

380
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:59,600
in the family group chat.

381
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,700
- Oh no...
- Where could she be?

382
00:18:02,767 --> 00:18:03,900
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

383
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:08,167
Nothing. We're at a dead end.

384
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:11,733
I really thought
we'd find something out.

385
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:14,733
Isn't it better
that we didn't find anything?

386
00:18:14,733 --> 00:18:15,867
Kiko...

387
00:18:15,867 --> 00:18:17,933
No,
my gut just won't let it go.

388
00:18:17,933 --> 00:18:20,700
I know it.
I can really feel it.

389
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,833
You're really holding on
to that hunch.

390
00:18:22,867 --> 00:18:25,800
Kiko, I know what I saw
when we were kids.

391
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,933
I really saw Mom
and Uncle Mike together.

392
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:29,600
Right? I've told you
about that before.

393
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:32,133
Yeah, yeah.
You've said that before.

394
00:18:32,133 --> 00:18:33,633
But what does that mean?

395
00:18:33,633 --> 00:18:35,067
Papa pursued Aunt Frida

396
00:18:35,067 --> 00:18:38,067
while she was
still married to Uncle Fred?

397
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:40,933
Gave her chocolates,
flowers, that kind of thing?

398
00:18:43,767 --> 00:18:45,000
Flowers...

399
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:50,767
Flowers!

401
00:18:50,767 --> 00:18:51,867
Flowers!

402
00:18:51,867 --> 00:18:54,533
Someone gave Mom flowers.

403
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:55,867
She said they were
<i> waling-waling.</i>

404
00:18:57,033 --> 00:18:58,933
Wait, when...
when did this happen?

405
00:18:58,933 --> 00:19:02,000
It was recent. She even thought
one of us gave them to her.

406
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:05,567
Oh... maybe Papa
wasn't really the one

407
00:19:05,567 --> 00:19:07,267
she had a relationship with?

408
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:09,800
Maybe it was another man,
and he's still alive.

409
00:19:10,767 --> 00:19:13,900
Who gave her the flowers?

410
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:20,000
Wait, is there a flower shop
near here?

411
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,800
Yes.

412
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:23,967
Two.

413
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:25,033
In town.

414
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:35,733
<i>One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight.</i>

415
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:36,833
<i>- And right...
- Yes, right!</i>

416
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:37,900
<i>- Right.
- Oh, okay.</i>

417
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:39,033
<i>- Perfect!
- Okay.</i>

418
00:19:39,033 --> 00:19:45,367
- "Wow, Hotel 88 looks fun"
- [BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

419
00:19:50,133 --> 00:19:51,500
[PHONE CHIMES]

420
00:19:52,467 --> 00:19:54,633
[MUSIC STOPS]

421
00:19:54,633 --> 00:19:55,967
[BRY]
<i> Bro, is this yours?</i>

422
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:57,767
<i> Is this your missing car?</i>

423
00:19:57,767 --> 00:20:04,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

424
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:08,933
"THAT'S IT!
WHERE DID YOU SEE IT?"

425
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,133
[LINE RINGING]

426
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:14,467
Bro, where'd they find the car?

427
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:16,533
[BRY] Bok tried
to have my friend sell it.

428
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:17,833
<i> He turned it down.</i>

429
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,733
What? Sell what?

430
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:23,067
How did that happen?

431
00:20:23,067 --> 00:20:25,467
[BRY]<i> He knows
</i> how Bok operates, Gio.

432
00:20:25,467 --> 00:20:27,667
Those bastards are a syndicate.

433
00:20:30,767 --> 00:20:32,567
What do you mean,
a syndicate?

434
00:20:32,567 --> 00:20:34,600
[BRY]
<i> They ask you to sell the car,</i>

435
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,633
<i>then they're the ones
who steal it too.</i>

436
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:38,633
<i>In the end,
you're the one who loses</i>

437
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:40,533
<i>because you end up
owing them.</i>

438
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:44,033
<i>Isn't that exactly what
Bok's been doing to you?</i>

439
00:20:45,533 --> 00:20:47,233
That bastard!

440
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:54,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

441
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:59,767
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

442
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:10,900
Uh... Miss?

443
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:14,533
Excuse me. Do you happen
to have waling-waling?

444
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:15,667
Like this.

445
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:18,833
[FLORIST]
Did you say waling-waling?

446
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:20,967
No one sells that.

447
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:23,033
What? Why not?

448
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:27,600
Because this flower is rare.

449
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:29,567
You can't just buy it anywhere.

450
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,033
You're right.

451
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:35,467
There are places where that
plant is already endangered.

452
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:38,867
Kiko...

453
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,267
I just remembered,
Dad told me

454
00:21:41,267 --> 00:21:45,133
this flower is too delicate
and takes a long time to grow.

455
00:21:45,167 --> 00:21:46,100
We're screwed.

456
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:48,067
What? How are we supposed
to find one now?

457
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:50,000
I don't know either, Kiko.

458
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,567
What do we do?

459
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,100
[FLORIST]
Wait.

460
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:57,700
I know someone
who grows that kind of plant.

461
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,633
Really?

462
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:02,033
Where?

463
00:22:05,133 --> 00:22:09,133
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

464
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:10,767
- Where's the guest in room 203?
- Huh?

465
00:22:10,767 --> 00:22:12,633
- This guest in room 203.
- [CHUCKLES]

466
00:22:12,633 --> 00:22:14,133
Chill, why the face?

467
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,233
He's by the pool area.

468
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:17,167
He even had these drinks
sent over.

469
00:22:17,167 --> 00:22:18,567
Gio, why?

470
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:22,567
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

471
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:25,633
Hey! Hey, Gio, what are you
going to do? Wait, Gio!

472
00:22:27,133 --> 00:22:29,200
Why'd you point him there?

473
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,267
He asked.

474
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:31,867
Wasn't I supposed to say?

475
00:22:31,867 --> 00:22:33,567
Did you see Gio's face?

476
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:35,600
Call Martin.
Right now, hurry!

477
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:39,633
[INAUDIBLE]

478
00:22:39,633 --> 00:22:41,800
- Yes!
- Yes!

479
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,300
[LAUGHS]

480
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,600
[GRUNTS]

481
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,833
- Ahh, that hits the spot.
- [GRUNTS]

482
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,900
What, want to order more?

483
00:22:53,267 --> 00:22:54,600
What?

484
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:57,000
Why don't we just buy
this resort?

485
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,600
- Whoo!
- You're just drunk, boss

486
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:00,767
Drunk? I'm not drunk.

487
00:23:00,767 --> 00:23:02,000
You're crazy.

488
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,933
You know what?

489
00:23:04,933 --> 00:23:07,233
This is mine!

490
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:10,700
I can easily buy this place,
man. Right?

491
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,833
What about you, man?
How much are you, huh?

492
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:13,733
Alright, alright.

493
00:23:13,733 --> 00:23:16,200
- 5 million pesos.
- 5 million pesos?

494
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,100
- You're weak, man.
- You're ugly, man.

495
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:19,900
- What about you?
- That's cheap!

496
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:21,933
- You, how much? How much?
- 10 million pesos.

497
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,800
That's more like it.

498
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:25,733
10 million, huh?

499
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:27,267
10 million?
5 million?

500
00:23:27,267 --> 00:23:29,300
I got you covered, guys.

501
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:30,367
[GRUNTS]

502
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,767
Dude! Hey!

503
00:23:32,767 --> 00:23:35,267
I'll buy your property, okay?

504
00:23:35,267 --> 00:23:36,833
[BLOW LANDS]

505
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:39,200
[BODY SPLASHES INTO WATER]

506
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,633
[WATER SPLASHING SOFTLY]

507
00:23:41,467 --> 00:23:45,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

508
00:23:49,633 --> 00:23:50,500
Is it here?

509
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,900
Yeah, I think.

510
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:57,600
It's what that old lady said.

511
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:04,933
Hello?

512
00:24:06,567 --> 00:24:07,600
Hello?

513
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,433
- Anybody there?
- Kiko-- Kiko, wait.

514
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:11,933
I think it's abandoned.

515
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:14,900
I think I know this place.

516
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:17,467
Why?

517
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:19,967
Have you been here before?

518
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,500
This is our driver's house.

519
00:24:25,433 --> 00:24:29,267
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

520
00:24:47,933 --> 00:24:50,000
<i>I'm not gonna pay
what you stole!</i>

521
00:24:50,767 --> 00:24:52,533
<i> Gio! That's enough!</i>

522
00:24:52,667 --> 00:24:54,033
<i> You judge our family so much,</i>

523
00:24:54,167 --> 00:24:56,133
<i>as if you don't start
your own fights.</i>

524
00:24:56,267 --> 00:24:58,700
<i>Why don't you manage
your brother's anger issues?</i>

525
00:24:58,833 --> 00:25:01,067
<i> You're all the same!</i>

526
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,433
<i> I haven't seen Kiko all day.</i>

527
00:25:03,567 --> 00:25:05,400
<i>Is that the flower
you were talking about?</i>

528
00:25:05,533 --> 00:25:07,967
- You're looking for her, right?
<i> - Where is she?</i>

529
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:11,267
<i> Jade! Run! Go!</i>

530
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,500
[PANTING]

